my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) The Manufacturer’s Manual must be consulted for procedures, tools, etc., prior to any maintenance or repairs being carried out; b) Permission must be obtained from Master and / or Chief Engineer; 
c) Safe Work Permit to be issued; 
d) Crew involved in the task to be briefed; e) Use of appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, goggles, etc.; 
f) Smoking is not permitted; g) Emergency exits, escape routes should be clear of any obstruction; 
h) Any machinery under maintenance/repair should have a warning notice posted on the controls; 
i) Machinery to be depressurised and isolated prior to any maintenance / repairs being carried out. 
j) All moving parts should be guarded; 
k) Crew should keep clear of all moving parts; 
l) Guards to be dismantled and mounted back immediately after the job is completed.

a) Machinery should be left to cool down for a sufficient time; 
b) Use of PPE: overalls, safety shoes, gloves, hard hat, etc.; 
c) Hot machinery / equipment must be cordoned off to prevent the crew from coming into contact with the surface.

a) The system to be depressurised and isolated prior to the dismantling of any parts e.g. hoses, pipes, etc.;
b) Drain the system before opening any machinery covers, were possible; 
c) All appropriate valves to be shut in order to stop supply of oil to the machinery; 
d) Remove any oil from machinery parts and tools which are being handled; 
e) Clean contaminated deck areas as soon as possible; 
f) When working with hydraulic oil, rubber gloves should be worn; 
g) Consult 'Dealing With Hazardous Substances' Risk Assessment.

a) Consult ‘Operating Handheld and Power Tools’ Risk Assessment, when applicable; 
b) Consult 'Operation of Bench or Fixed Tools' Risk Assessment, when applicable; 
c) Consult ‘Operating High Pressure Hydraulic Tools’ Risk Assessment, when applicable.

a) Adequate lighting to be provided. Use portable lighting if required; 
b) Guard rails that have been removed should be mounted back as soon as possible; 
c) Any opening in deck e.g. removed grating, opened manhole, etc. should be secured with guard rails/ropes and adequately lit; 
d) Parts, tools, etc., must not obstruct the walkway.

a) Suitable lifting equipment and chocks should be used when opening manholes, removing floor plates; 
b) Fingers should not be used to align holes in machinery being mounted or reassembled; 
c) Consult ‘Manual Handling’ Risk Assessment; 
d) Consult 'Handling Heavy Parts' Risk Assessment.

a) Crew to wear adequate PPE to existing temperatures in the machinery space; 
b) Use of mechanical fans;
c) Breaks should be taken at regular intervals; 
d) Drink sufficient water to avoid dehydration.
